download

DimensionsResult download(DownloadCommandDetails det)
Runs the Download command in a mode determined by the settings in the DownloadCommandDetails/code>DownloadCommandDetails bean. Returns a DownloadCommandDetails object containing either a list of information for each item like Status, Command to execute, etc. which then can be passed on to the user or executed directly or a String message if the command is directly execuuted.

Parameters:
det - DownloadCommandDetails bean
Returns:
DimensionsResult DimensionsResult containing mesage from execution or a List of FileToUpload objects containing the results

downloadExec

DimensionsResult downloadExec(java.lang.String baselineDirectory,
                              java.lang.String userDirectory,
                              java.lang.String codePage,
                              java.lang.String logFile,
                              boolean recursive,
                              boolean touch,
                              boolean expand,
                              boolean overwrite,
                              boolean checkConflict)
Runs the Download command in an executing mode. Returns a DimensionsResult. All results of all commands executed can be retained by specifying a log file.

Parameters:
baselineDirectory - the directory in the baseline that should be downloaded (Pass in empty string if root directory should be taken
userDirectory - the directory in the user area that the baseline should be compared to
codePage - Name of the codepage to be used. If not supplied, standard codepage is used.
logFile - full Path of log file
recursive - Whether all subdirectories of the baseline should be downloaded as well
touch - Whether the files should get the current timestamp (true) or the timestamp stored in the database (false)
expand - Whether the substitution variables should get expanded when fetching the items
overwrite - Whether locally changed files should be overwritten
checkConflict - Whether download should check for conflicts for each item revision to be fetched. If any unresolved conflicts are found, Dimensions issues a warning and ignores the corresponding revision.
Returns:
DimensionsResult result

downloadExec

DimensionsResult downloadExec(java.util.List filesToDownload,
                              java.lang.String userDirectory,
                              java.lang.String relativeLocation,
                              java.lang.String codePage,
                              java.lang.String logFile,
                              boolean touch,
                              boolean expand,
                              boolean overwrite,
                              boolean checkConflict)
Runs the Download command in an executing mode. Returns a DimensionsResult. All results of all commands executed can be retained by specifying a log file.

Parameters:
filesToDownload - List of FileToUpload instances that should be downloaded
userDirectory - the directory in the user area that the baseline should be compared to
relativeLocation - An offset in the workset. E.g. getting c:\workspace\projfoo\junit\awtui\AboutDialog.java, which has workset path bar/yuk/acme/junit/awtui/AboutDialog.java requires specifying the files in the filesToDownload list parameter in the form c:\workspace\projfoo\junit\awtui\AboutDialog.java, the userDirectory parameter in the form c:\workspace\projfoo\ and the relativeLocation parameter in the form bar\yuk\acme (Pass in an empty string if no offset is required.)
codePage - Name of the codepage to be used. If not supplied, standard codepage is used.
logFile - full Path of log file
touch - Whether the files should get the current timestamp (true) or the timestamp stored in the database (false)
expand - Whether the substitution variables should get expanded when fetching the items
overwrite - Whether locally changed files should be overwritten
checkConflict - Whether download should check for conflicts for each item revision to be fetched. If any unresolved conflicts are found, Dimensions issues a warning and ignores the corresponding revision.
Returns:
DimensionsResult result

Runs the Download command in a non-executing modus. Returns information for each item like Status, Command to execute, etc. which then can be passed on to the user or executed directly.

Parameters:
baselineDirectory - the directory in the baseline that should be downloaded (Pass in empty string if root directory should be taken
userDirectory - the directory in the user area that the baseline should be compared to
codePage - Name of the codepage to be used. If not supplied, standard codepage is used.
logFile - Path of log file for output xml file. If not supplied, temporary file is used and deleted
recursive - Whether all subdirectories of the project should be downloaded as well
touch - Whether the files should get the current timestamp (true) or the timestamp stored in the database (false)
expand - Whether the substitution variables should get expanded when fetching the items
overwrite - Whether locally changed files should be overwritten
checkConflict - Whether download should check for conflicts for each item revision to be fetched. If any unresolved conflicts are found, Dimensions issues a warning and ignores the corresponding revision.
Returns:
List List of FileToUpload objects containing the results

deploy

@Deprecated
DimensionsResult deploy(Project project,
                                   java.lang.String stage,
                                   java.lang.String comment)
Deprecated. As of CM 12.1, use promote(Project, String, String) or demote(Project, String, String) instead.

Deploys a baseline to the given stage using CM 2009 R2 stage deployment. Promotion or demotion to a stage has replaced stage deployment as of CM 12.1 or later.

Parameters:
project - Specifies the root project to be used for the stage deployment.
stage - The target stage to deploy to.
comment - The comment applied to the stage deployment.
Returns:
DimensionsResult The result of the operation.

build

DimensionsResult build(java.lang.String areaName,
                       java.lang.String buildConfigurationName,
                       java.util.List buildOptions,
                       java.util.List requestIds,
                       java.util.List targetNames,
                       boolean capture,
                       boolean batchMode,
                       boolean buildClean,
                       boolean touch)
Build baseline.

Parameters:
areaName - Dimensions area to be used for the build.
buildConfigurationName - build configuration.
buildOptions - build options.
requestIds - request to which the new items created from the built final targets are to be related in-Response-to if required by change management rules.
targetNames - list of targets to be built.
capture - specifies whether built targets are to be collected.
batchMode - run build in batch mode.
buildClean - area is to be cleaned of targets before the build process begins.
touch - apply system date/time to downloaded files.
Returns:
DimensionsResult The result of the operation.
